<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,310,592,618]" box="[189,310,592,618]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,310,592,618]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,310,592,618]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,1399,639,848]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
Differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Tebbitt (Tebbit 2005)" authorityName="Tebbitt (Tebbitt" authorityYear="2005" box="[342,774,639,666]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scottii">
<emphasis box="[342,519,640,665]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Begonia scottii</emphasis>
Tebbitt (Tebbit 2005)
</taxonomicName>
in bearing fruit in clusters of 10–15 (not 2 or 4), with the fruit being fleshier and rounder, with ridges rather than small wings. The infructescence in terms of fruit number and shape is more similar to that of 
<taxonomicName authority="Blume (Blume 1827)" authorityName="Blume (Blume" authorityYear="1827" box="[826,1260,712,738]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="multangula">
<emphasis box="[826,996,712,738]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">B. multangula</emphasis>
Blume (
<bibRefCitation author="Blume C. L." box="[1102,1252,712,738]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" refId="ref17665" refString="Blume C. L. 1827. Enumeratio Plantarum Javae et insularum adjacentium minus cognitarum vel novarum ex herbariis Reinwardtii, Kuhlii, Hasseltii et Blumii curavit Carol. Ludov. Blume. Apud J. W. van Leeuwen, Lugduni Batavorum [Leiden]. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 44901" type="book" year="1827">Blume 1827</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, which has lobed leaves that are either subglabrous or have white hairs (not pink), and apical (not basal) more lax infructesences. The flowers have pink centres to the tepals (uniform white in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tebbitt (Tebbitt" authorityYear="2005" box="[1107,1212,785,810]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Begoniaceae" genus="Begonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scottii">
<emphasis box="[1107,1212,785,810]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">B. scottii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and the leaves have deep pink hairs (not white).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="30.[189,324,887,913]" box="[189,324,887,913]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
